1. YOU KEEP STRESSING!
Stress is a killer & can stunt your hair growth. You may not even realize stress is causing your hair loss. I know it’s hard but try to stop stressing.

2. YOU ARE NOT GETTING TRIMMED REGULARLY.
You should get your hair trimmed every 2 months to avoid split ends.

3. YOU ARE NOT USING THE RIGHT PRODUCT TYPE!
Figure out your hair type, hair porosity, density, curl pattern etc & choose the best high quality products that work for YOU!

4. YOU DON’T HAVE A GOOD HAIR REGIMEN!
* You don’t wash your hair often 
* You don’t use the right products
* You don’t wash & condition your hair correctly
* You don’t nourish and hydrate your hair
  you don’t wear protective styles
* Establish a good hair care routine & watch your hair flourish!

5. YOU KEEP COLORING YOUR HAIR!
Color compromises the integrity of your hair making it fragile and prone to breakage each time you color it.

6. YOU ARE WEARING TIGHT PONYTAILS!
Avoid wearing tight ponytails with elastic ties at the same spot in your hair - try silk scrunches tying your hair loosely or using clips.

7. YOU HAVE A MEDICAL CONDITION CONTRIBUTING TO BREAKAGE OR THE MEDICATION YOU ARE TAKING.
Your health is important and can affect the growth of your hair. Certain health conditions may cause breakage to your hair as well as certain medications you may be taking.

8. YOU ARE EXPERIENCING HAIR LOSS DUE TO HEREDITARY REASONS!
Sometimes you may experience hair loss at a later stage in your life from hereditary reasons.
For example, you may not have traction alopecia but could cause hair loss at later age due to DNA. 

9. YOU DON’T WEAR PROTECTIVE STYLES!
Protective styles will give your hair a break and allow it to grow while serving looks at the same
time. Research styles that may work for your hair that fits your style/look. Preserve your hair sometimes!

10. YOU HAVE HEAT DAMAGE.
You continuously fail to use heat protection products all while using cheap tools. All hair tools are not created equal. Always buy the best curated hair tools and quality hair products.
